# Styling Rules

## Primary Styling Method

Use **Tailwind CSS utility classes** as the primary styling method:

```typescript
<div className="flex flex-col justify-center items-center self-stretch cursor-pointer hover:shadow-sm transition-shadow py-4 gap-1 flex-1 rounded-lg border border-ui-border-gray">
  {/* content */}
</div>
```

## Design System Colors

### Brand Colors
Use these for primary brand elements:

```css
/* In Tailwind classes */
text-brand-purple-gray     /* #6E6B86 - Secondary text */
text-brand-orchid-purple   /* #6C5CE7 - Primary actions, links */
text-brand-dark-text       /* #212121 - Primary text */
text-brand-tarmac-grey     /* #475161 - Subdued text */
```

### UI Colors
Use these for UI elements:

```css
border-ui-border-gray      /* #DDE3EE - Borders */
bg-ui-light-bg             /* #F7F9FC - Light backgrounds */
bg-ui-tulip-purple         /* #F9F8FF - Subtle purple backgrounds */
```

### Semantic Colors
Use CSS variables for semantic colors:

```css
bg-background              /* Main background */
text-foreground            /* Main text */
bg-primary                 /* Primary actions */
bg-muted                   /* Muted/disabled states */
border-border              /* Default borders */
```

## Typography Scale

Use the custom typography classes:

```css
text-body-p1    /* 16px, 150% line-height, 0.16px letter-spacing */
text-body-p2    /* 14px, 150% line-height */
text-body-p3    /* 12px, 150% line-height, 0.24px letter-spacing */
text-stat-count /* 28px, 150% line-height - For large numbers */
```

Example:
```typescript
<div className="text-stat-count font-semibold text-center font-inter text-brand-dark-text">
  {count}
</div>
<div className="text-body-p2 font-normal text-center font-inter text-brand-purple-gray">
  {label}
</div>
```

## Font Family

Always use Inter font family:

```css
font-inter  /* Inter, sans-serif */
```

## Spacing and Sizing

### Custom Spacing
```css
w-stat-card    /* 192px */
h-stat-card    /* 206px */
```

### Common Patterns
```css
p-4            /* 16px padding */
gap-4          /* 16px gap */
gap-1          /* 4px gap */
py-6           /* 24px vertical padding */
```

## Animation Classes

### Built-in Animations
```css
animate-fade-in      /* Fade in with translateY */
animate-shimmer      /* Shimmer effect for loading */
animate-wave         /* Wave effect for skeletons */
animate-breathing    /* Pulse/breathing effect */
animate-pulse        /* Standard pulse */
```

### Animation Delays
Use inline styles for staggered animations:

```typescript
<div
  className="animate-shimmer"
  style={{ animationDelay: `${delay}ms` }}
/>
```

## Loading Skeleton Pattern

```typescript
function SkeletonBox({ className = "", delay = 0 }: { className?: string; delay?: number }) {
  return (
    <div
      className={`bg-gradient-to-r from-muted via-muted/50 to-muted bg-[length:200%_100%] animate-shimmer rounded ${className}`}
      style={{ animationDelay: `${delay}ms` }}
    />
  );
}
```

