## Button Styling

### Text Button
```typescript
<button className="cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-none px-4 py-2 text-body-p2 font-semibold font-inter text-brand-orchid-purple">
```

### Icon Button
```typescript
<button className="p-1 hover:bg-muted rounded transition-colors duration-200">
```

## Transitions

Use consistent transition classes:
```css
transition-shadow          /* For shadow effects */
transition-colors          /* For color changes */
duration-200               /* 200ms duration */
```

## CSS File Organization

- `src/index.css` - Global styles, Tailwind imports, CSS variables
- `src/containers/index.css` - Container-specific reusable styles
- `src/containers/*/ComponentName.css` - Component-specific styles (use sparingly)

## CSS Variables

Define in `src/index.css` under `@layer base`:

```css
@layer base {
  :root {
    --background: 0 0% 100%;
    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --primary: 221.2 83.2% 53.3%;
    --muted: 210 40% 96%;
    --border: 214.3 31.8% 91.4%;
    --radius: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

## Avoiding CSS-in-JS

Prefer Tailwind classes over inline styles. Only use inline styles for:
- Dynamic values (animation delays)
- Values not available in Tailwind config

```typescript
// Good - Tailwind classes
<div className="w-8 h-8 text-primary" />

// Acceptable - dynamic value
<div style={{ animationDelay: `${index * 100}ms` }} />

// Avoid - static styles inline
<div style={{ width: '32px', height: '32px' }} />
```

